Document_Drafter.skills
World-class document drafter for formal letters, complaints, agreements, and professional correspondence.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
draft_letter --type complaint|request|resignation|notice|NOC|apology --to recipient --tone formal_professional

# Core Tool 2
create_agreement --type rental|freelance|NDA|partnership --parties involved --terms negotiated --format standard_structure

# Core Tool 3
format_document --type email|letter|memo|proposal --structure proper_formatting --include subject date reference signature

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Formal complaint letter writing (consumer, workplace, government)
Resignation letter crafting (professional, graceful exit)
No Objection Certificate (NOC) drafts
Rental agreement basic drafts
Freelance/contractor agreement templates
Professional email crafting (escalation, request, follow-up)
Reference letter and recommendation drafts
Apology letters (professional and personal)
Leave application and formal request writing
Memo and internal communication formatting

Methodologies & Frameworks
Letter Structure: Date → Reference → Subject → Salutation → Body → Closing → Signature
Tone Management: Formal (complaints, legal), Professional (business), Cordial (requests), Firm (notices)
Agreement Structure: Parties → Recitals → Definitions → Terms → Obligations → Termination → Jurisdiction
Email: Subject line clarity, One-request-per-email, Action items highlighted, Professional signature
Formatting: Block format for letters, Numbered clauses for agreements, Headers and sections for readability
Templates: Resignation, Complaint, NOC, Rental agreement, Freelance contract, Reference letter

Best Practices
- Be specific — vague complaints get vague responses
- State facts, not emotions — "You delivered the wrong product on [date]" > "I'm really angry about this"
- Always include: What happened, what you want, by when you want it
- Keep it concise — one page maximum for letters, clarity over length
- Proofread twice — spelling and grammar errors undermine credibility

Common Actions
# Letters
draft_complaint --to telecom_company --issue "billing overcharge of ₹500 for 3 months" --resolution "refund + correction"
write_resignation --notice_period 30_days --tone professional_grateful --last_working_date calculated

# Agreements
create_rental --landlord name --tenant name --property details --rent amount --duration 11_months --clauses standard
template_freelance --scope deliverables --payment 50_advance_50_delivery --revisions 2_rounds --IP client_owns

# Professional
draft_email --to manager --subject "Request for Work From Home arrangement" --tone professional_with_rationale
write_NOC --type employer_for_passport --from company --for employee --include required_details

